The paper deals with log-likelihood estimation in computational models, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions specific applications in computational biology and neuroscience, which suggests a focus on neural networks and other related models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
